and lead them through the arm movements of Eagle Pose with their breath.";i:28;s:115:"As they inhale instruct them to raise their arms to shoulder height with their palms facing away from their bodies.";i:29;s:62:"Varying the shoulder stretch once your arms are in eagle pose.";i:30;s:149:"Once your arms are in eagle pose you can vary the shoulder stretch by reaching your forearms forwards below left or lifting your elbows below center.";i:31;s:109:"You can also tilt your arms to upper arm side to give the upper arm an external rotation stretch below right.";i:32;s:70:"Step Four Refine Hug your legs together and sit back as in chair pose.";i:33;s:109:"Lift your elbows to shoulder height and settle the heads of your arm bones back toward your shoulder sockets.";i:34;s:115:"Maintain that and reach your hands forward away from you to create more stretch between your upper shoulder blades.";i:35;s:29:"Relax your face and your jaw.";i:36;s:89:"Hi everyone - I recently partnered with Stayfree for a yoga initiative that ended on 312.";i:37;s:67:"If you are interested in hearing about Stayfree click through to h.";i:38;s:129:"I thought you might want the time stamps for the different poses for those who want to refer back to this multiple times like me.";i:39;s:78:"I also tried to comment on your youtube video but the comments are turned off.";i:40;s:44:"148 Legs 1 227 Legs 2 303 Legs 3 333 Legs 4.";i:41;s:43:"Cow Face Pose with Eagle Arms Instructions.";i:42;s:94:"Sit on the floor and cross your left leg over the right stacking one knee on top of the other.";i:43;s:101:"Bend your elbows raise and cross your forearms so that the palms of your hands are facing each other.";i:44;s:92:"Stay in cow face pose with eagle arms for 30 seconds and then repeat with the arms and legs.";i:45;s:62:"You can place a prop under your buttocks to support your hips.";i:46;s:51:"Bring your arms in front of you bent to 90 degrees.";i:47;s:135:"Swing your left arm beneath the right and spiral your right hand and forearm around the left until your hands touch in Eagle Pose arms.";i:48;s:20:"Hold for 10 breaths.";i:49;s:37:"See alsoHalf Lord of the Fishes Pose.";i:50;s:30:"Pose in the Eagle progression.";i:51;s:100:"This is the full wrap of the Eagle pose and it is quite challenging for anyone with shoulder issues.";i:52;s:38:"Make sure to keep both shoulders down.";i:53;s:64:"My right shoulder is slightly lifted and could be lowered a bit.";i:54;s:23:"Benefits of Eagle Pose.";i:55;s:36:"The benefits of Eagle pose are vast.";i:56;s:68:"Done properly and consistently the most noticeable benefits include.";i:57;s:36:"Stronger arms legs knees and ankles.";i:58;s:64:"Open shoulder joints creating space between the shoulder blades.";i:59;s:22:"Open hips and IT band.";i:60;s:36:"Increased circulation to all joints.";i:61;s:35:"Improved digestion and elimination.";}}